1
00:00:58,601 --> 00:00:59,435
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

2
00:00:59,518 --> 00:01:01,020
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

3
00:01:19,622 --> 00:01:20,956
YOO JAE-HA
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU

4
00:01:22,124 --> 00:01:23,667
Do you want to listen to it first?

5
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:25,711
No, please. Go ahead.

6
00:01:28,547 --> 00:01:29,673
I'll get going.

7
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:31,467
Well…

8
00:01:34,553 --> 00:01:37,515
I'd like to apologize
if I offended you the other day.

9
00:01:40,726 --> 00:01:41,936
It's fine.

10
00:01:42,019 --> 00:01:43,395
It's in the past now.

11
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:49,360
Do you like Yoo Jae-ha?

12
00:01:49,443 --> 00:01:50,820
YOO JAE-HA
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU

13
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:52,571
Yes.

14
00:01:53,197 --> 00:01:55,491
"Because I Love You" is my favorite.

15
00:01:55,574 --> 00:01:56,492
What song do you like?

16
00:01:56,575 --> 00:01:59,078
I like the same song too.

17
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,414
Whenever I come here,

18
00:02:02,498 --> 00:02:04,124
I always listen to it on vinyl.

19
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:06,502
If you listen to the remastered CD,

20
00:02:06,585 --> 00:02:09,213
the tempo feels oddly slower,
so it doesn't feel the same.

21
00:02:10,965 --> 00:02:13,968
I heard that's a technical error
that occurs when transferring it to CD.

22
00:02:14,844 --> 00:02:17,096
Oh, so that's why.

23
00:02:17,179 --> 00:02:19,306
It's a coincidence caused by a mistake,

24
00:02:19,390 --> 00:02:21,809
but I like it
because it suits a breakup song.

25
00:02:23,102 --> 00:02:25,020
"I will give you everything I have

26
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:27,189
now that you've come back to me."

27
00:02:28,357 --> 00:02:30,526
Isn't it about breaking up
then getting back together?

28
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,945
It's more the speaker's wish and regret

29
00:02:33,028 --> 00:02:34,905
that it's what he'd do
if they ever came back.

30
00:02:35,281 --> 00:02:38,534
But now I realize

31
00:02:38,617 --> 00:02:41,203
YOO JAE-HA
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU

32
00:02:42,413 --> 00:02:49,169
I belong to you only

33
00:02:49,712 --> 00:02:56,719
Now that you have returned to me

34
00:03:00,055 --> 00:03:01,181
I will give you everything…

35
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:02,349
After hearing what he said,

36
00:03:03,517 --> 00:03:04,894
it really does sound different.

37
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,066
I guess

38
00:03:12,693 --> 00:03:14,028
I haven't been able to let you go.

39
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:23,871
We will never say goodbye

40
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:26,081
YEONG-MOOK REPAIR SERVICES

41
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:34,256
Because I love only you

42
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,010
Mr. Kang!

43
00:03:38,093 --> 00:03:41,221
Because I love you

44
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:48,771
Did you come here a lot as a kid?

45
00:03:49,939 --> 00:03:50,856
Yes.

46
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:53,400
When I bombed a test
or didn't want to go to cram school,

47
00:03:53,484 --> 00:03:54,652
I'd usually hide out here.

48
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:58,113
We might've
run into each other here, right?

49
00:03:58,197 --> 00:03:59,573
Come to think of it,

50
00:03:59,657 --> 00:04:02,159
I think I saw a girl
who looked like a troublemaker.

51
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:06,038
Well, I think I saw an older guy
who looked incredibly boring.

52
00:04:06,121 --> 00:04:07,539
That probably wasn't me, then.

53
00:04:07,623 --> 00:04:09,667
People said my face alone
keeps them entertained.

54
00:04:19,343 --> 00:04:20,344
Dad?

55
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:22,680
That's the neighbor's door opening.

56
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,516
That scared me.

57
00:04:26,058 --> 00:04:27,142
I thought it was my dad.

58
00:04:27,226 --> 00:04:30,145
Shouldn't we tell your father, though?

59
00:04:30,229 --> 00:04:31,605
He'd probably feel betrayed.

60
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:33,565
That's true, but…

61
00:04:34,733 --> 00:04:36,193
He's a decent kid.

62
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:37,903
And a lonely one.

63
00:04:38,529 --> 00:04:41,448
What would you think
if I dated someone like that?

64
00:04:43,492 --> 00:04:44,451
I'm not sure.

65
00:04:44,535 --> 00:04:47,246
You said he's a good guy.
Why are you hesitating?

66
00:04:47,329 --> 00:04:49,707
That's a whole different issue.

67
00:04:50,332 --> 00:04:51,959
I don't think this is the right time.

68
00:04:53,002 --> 00:04:54,628
Then tell me when you think it's time.

69
00:04:55,421 --> 00:04:56,547
Okay.

70
00:04:59,675 --> 00:05:01,010
It's all set.

71
00:05:01,093 --> 00:05:01,927
Want to listen?

72
00:05:02,011 --> 00:05:02,970
Yes.

73
00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:21,155
It's working!

74
00:05:26,744 --> 00:05:28,704
It sounds just like it used to.

75
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:31,373
It sounds so beautiful.

76
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:43,093
I know a photo can't capture sound,

77
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:44,762
but let's take one as a keepsake.

78
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:46,513
Okay.

79
00:05:56,523 --> 00:06:01,070
EPISODE 10
DON'T KNOW THE ANSWER, STILL CLOCKING IN!

80
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:47,449
Should I reach out to domestic stores
with the same concept?

81
00:06:47,533 --> 00:06:50,035
Yes, and let's propose
with the condition that we handle

82
00:06:50,119 --> 00:06:51,912
the system integration
and content updates.

83
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:53,872
I'll manage the overseas side.

84
00:06:53,956 --> 00:06:56,375
Ms. Cha and Mr. Jeon,
please take care of the domestic side.

85
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:57,543
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

86
00:06:57,626 --> 00:07:01,088
Also, I have a business trip
out of town today.

87
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:02,798
-A business trip?
-Yes.

88
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:06,218
An international buyer who missed the demo
requested a last-minute meeting.

89
00:07:06,969 --> 00:07:09,012
I'll be in Pohang today and tomorrow.

90
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:12,599
Please make sure everything
runs smoothly while I'm away.

91
00:07:12,683 --> 00:07:13,600
Yes, sir.

92
00:07:13,684 --> 00:07:15,185
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

93
00:07:27,614 --> 00:07:28,448
Hey, hey.

94
00:07:29,283 --> 00:07:30,742
Why? What's wrong?

95
00:07:30,826 --> 00:07:32,077
Is something wrong?

96
00:07:32,161 --> 00:07:34,079
It's the Legal Team.

97
00:07:34,163 --> 00:07:36,748
I wrote "world's first"
because it's the world's first,

98
00:07:36,832 --> 00:07:38,458
but they told me they need proof.

99
00:07:38,542 --> 00:07:39,918
What proof?

100
00:07:40,002 --> 00:07:41,420
As far as we know, it is the first.

101
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:42,838
Exactly.

102
00:07:43,672 --> 00:07:45,799
They asked me if I've combed through
every tiny company

103
00:07:45,883 --> 00:07:47,467
on the other side of the world too.

104
00:07:49,052 --> 00:07:51,054
That team's always so conservative.

105
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:52,973
It won't work
no matter how much you explain.

106
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:54,183
Give up and change the wording.

107
00:07:55,392 --> 00:07:57,060
They're the absolute worst.

108
00:07:57,144 --> 00:07:58,937
Did you find the lead
for the web drama series?

109
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:01,481
It's Cho Ga-eul.

110
00:08:01,565 --> 00:08:03,066
Who's "Show Ga-eul"?

111
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,151
It's "Cho" Ga-eul.

112
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:05,235
Cho Ga-eul?

113
00:08:06,028 --> 00:08:09,406
He's the vocalist of that band
that's blowing up right now.

114
00:08:10,616 --> 00:08:11,867
Ms. Cha, you know him, right?

115
00:08:13,202 --> 00:08:14,620
Yeah. That's great news.

116
00:08:15,245 --> 00:08:16,079
Right?

117
00:08:17,915 --> 00:08:20,584
Everything would be perfect
if it weren't for the Legal Team.

118
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:22,836
Now I have to rewrite the PR materials.

119
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:25,214
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

120
00:08:25,297 --> 00:08:27,090
Be the Clock-out Fairy today.

121
00:08:30,594 --> 00:08:32,971
All right, I'm clocking out
on the dot today.

122
00:08:34,056 --> 00:08:36,516
Wow, as soon as Mr. Kang's gone.

123
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,476
I'm leaving too.

124
00:08:38,352 --> 00:08:39,186
Really?

125
00:08:42,314 --> 00:08:43,440
See you.

126
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:44,358
Seriously?

127
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:47,778
You should finish up quickly
and get home too.

128
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:49,363
Wow, so much for loyalty.

129
00:08:51,406 --> 00:08:52,908
How am I supposed to finish all this?

130
00:08:56,745 --> 00:08:57,579
Mr. Kang?

131
00:08:57,663 --> 00:08:58,956
Did you leave the office?

132
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:01,625
Yes, I'm on my way home right now.

133
00:09:02,417 --> 00:09:03,377
What about you?

134
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:05,128
I'm in Busan right now.

135
00:09:06,255 --> 00:09:07,297
Not Pohang?

136
00:09:07,381 --> 00:09:08,590
Right.

137
00:09:08,674 --> 00:09:10,425
An old classmate
who came as a buyer at the demo

138
00:09:10,509 --> 00:09:11,802
said he's in Busan,

139
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:14,763
so I came over
after the meeting in Pohang.

140
00:09:14,846 --> 00:09:17,766
He must be a very close friend
for you to rush all the way to Busan.

141
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:20,519
He threatened me,
saying he might not sign the contract.

142
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:23,146
So it's just business.

143
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:26,608
I'm out here doing sales for our team,
Sr. Associate Cha.

144
00:09:29,111 --> 00:09:31,280
Keep up the good work, Manager Kang.

145
00:09:31,363 --> 00:09:32,823
I'll call you when I'm back at the hotel.

146
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:34,658
Okay.

147
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,371
Who was that? Soo-jin?

148
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,540
No, my girlfriend.

149
00:09:41,623 --> 00:09:42,916
Oh.

150
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,001
What?

151
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:45,585
What the heck?

152
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:49,464
Ms. Choi and I got divorced
less than a year after we got married.

153
00:09:50,215 --> 00:09:51,133
Wow.

154
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:52,968
I had no idea.

155
00:09:54,303 --> 00:09:56,263
Gosh, I think I slipped up
big time to Soo-jin.

156
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:59,808
I asked her how she's finding
working with her husband.

157
00:10:00,934 --> 00:10:01,935
She'll understand.

158
00:10:03,979 --> 00:10:05,188
But why did you break up?

159
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:07,232
You guys never fought once
while you were dating.

160
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:10,068
Everyone was so jealous,
saying you guys are like unicorns.

161
00:10:10,152 --> 00:10:11,028
Were we?

162
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:17,701
So you're just colleagues
and nothing more now?

163
00:10:18,827 --> 00:10:19,661
Yeah.

164
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,456
She actually got remarried recently.

165
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,166
What about you?

166
00:10:24,249 --> 00:10:26,668
Are you thinking about marriage
with your girlfriend too?

167
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:44,186
Oh, she's here.

168
00:10:44,269 --> 00:10:45,729
What's going on?

169
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,814
My place just got burgled.

170
00:10:47,898 --> 00:10:48,899
Burgled?

171
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:50,359
The upstairs unit got hit too.

172
00:10:50,942 --> 00:10:52,944
You should go inside and check as well.

173
00:10:53,028 --> 00:10:54,029
Let's go in.

174
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:55,822
Huh?

175
00:11:04,373 --> 00:11:06,124
-Take some photos first.
-Okay.

176
00:11:29,314 --> 00:11:31,858
A burglar broke into my house.

177
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:45,831
Ms. Ji-yoon, you should go to my place.

178
00:11:53,964 --> 00:11:56,174
When you get there,
drink some hot tea first.

179
00:11:57,259 --> 00:11:59,302
The light blue container
has chamomile in it.

180
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:00,762
CHAMOMILE

181
00:12:06,101 --> 00:12:09,020
Make yourself at home and get some rest.

182
00:12:09,604 --> 00:12:10,814
You're safe there.

183
00:12:13,775 --> 00:12:14,776
It's so warm.

184
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:31,751
CHA JI-YOON
SHE MAKES ME SMILE

185
00:12:31,835 --> 00:12:32,878
Wait…

186
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:34,671
What's that?

187
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:41,136
CHA JI-YOON
SHE MAKES ME SMILE

188
00:13:00,322 --> 00:13:01,156
Ms. Ji-yoon?

189
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,286
KANG SI-WOO
MAKES ME SMILE TOO!

190
00:13:06,369 --> 00:13:08,455
Kang Si-woo makes me smile too!

191
00:13:14,252 --> 00:13:15,670
Huh? Mr. Kang?

192
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,340
How did you get here at this hour?

193
00:13:18,924 --> 00:13:20,592
I managed to catch the last train.

194
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:21,843
You must've been terrified.

195
00:13:24,763 --> 00:13:25,764
Yes,

196
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:28,892
so you'll have to forgive me
for wearing your clothes.

197
00:13:29,684 --> 00:13:31,228
I was so scared I couldn't pack any.

198
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,730
Everything is fine as long as you're safe.

199
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:36,149
You're my rock.

200
00:13:40,946 --> 00:13:43,281
Did you leave your work unfinished
because of me?

201
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:45,158
Do you think I'm the type to do that?

202
00:13:46,326 --> 00:13:47,160
Nope.

203
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:50,205
Thank you for coming.

204
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:51,706
Ms. Ji-yoon,

205
00:13:53,041 --> 00:13:54,668
stay here for the time being.

206
00:13:56,419 --> 00:13:57,712
For the peace of my mind.

207
00:13:58,338 --> 00:14:00,715
Let's look for your new place
while you stay here.

208
00:14:02,926 --> 00:14:04,219
Am I moving?

209
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:06,346
I'd like it if you did.

210
00:14:07,973 --> 00:14:10,559
I was planning to move
once my lease is up anyway.

211
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:13,061
Even before the break-in?

212
00:14:14,271 --> 00:14:15,105
Yes.

213
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:18,525
I want to create
new memories in a new home.

214
00:14:21,695 --> 00:14:22,696
Don't move too far away.

215
00:14:23,405 --> 00:14:24,322
Of course I won't.

216
00:14:25,115 --> 00:14:26,950
I plan on staying glued to your side.

217
00:14:58,356 --> 00:14:59,274
Hey.

218
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:02,027
It'd be great to do it at my place,

219
00:15:02,110 --> 00:15:03,528
but we have a patient here.

220
00:15:04,321 --> 00:15:05,739
For goodness' sake.

221
00:15:05,822 --> 00:15:09,075
I'll prep the garlic and green onions
and bring them over.

222
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:10,243
Yes.

223
00:15:15,332 --> 00:15:16,875
I'll call you back.

224
00:15:21,379 --> 00:15:22,380
You're home early.

225
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:27,010
What are you doing?

226
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:28,345
What?

227
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:36,227
Am I a joke to you?

228
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:42,817
I told you to leave the cast alone!

229
00:15:42,901 --> 00:15:45,195
You have to keep it still
for it to heal quickly!

230
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:49,115
And then we can
finally go and see my lawyer.

231
00:15:55,330 --> 00:15:56,456
Were you

232
00:15:57,332 --> 00:15:58,958
wrapping this or unwrapping this?

233
00:15:59,042 --> 00:16:00,126
Geez.

234
00:16:04,714 --> 00:16:08,051
I'm making kimchi
at the laundromat lady's house tomorrow,

235
00:16:08,968 --> 00:16:10,845
so you and Joon-su
should order jjajangmyeon or whatever.

236
00:16:10,929 --> 00:16:13,223
Shouldn't I come with you and help out?

237
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,225
What, in this state?

238
00:16:17,852 --> 00:16:21,064
Just take some kimchi over to Ji-yoon
once your cast is off.

239
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,031
By the way,

240
00:16:31,574 --> 00:16:33,076
is something going on with Ji-yoon?

241
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:34,369
Why?

242
00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:35,328
It's just…

243
00:16:36,705 --> 00:16:38,206
She seems to have a lot on her mind.

244
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:40,750
Is she seeing someone?

245
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:45,505
She asked me what kind of guy I'd like her
to date, and I found that weird.

246
00:16:48,842 --> 00:16:50,301
Is she dating some weirdo?

247
00:16:50,385 --> 00:16:51,428
A weirdo?

248
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:54,806
A young guy Joon-su's age, or a slacker,

249
00:16:54,889 --> 00:16:56,349
or maybe a divorcé, or…

250
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:59,018
a guy she's embarrassed to talk about.

251
00:17:00,937 --> 00:17:02,772
Go poke around
when you drop off the kimchi.

252
00:17:02,856 --> 00:17:03,690
Should I?

253
00:17:03,773 --> 00:17:04,691
Yeah.

254
00:17:04,774 --> 00:17:05,650
Okay.

255
00:17:05,734 --> 00:17:07,318
-Yeah.
-Understood.

256
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,908
If you're bored, peel some garlic.

257
00:17:16,286 --> 00:17:17,120
Okay.

258
00:17:19,164 --> 00:17:22,667
All right,
this is absolutely the last one.

259
00:17:22,751 --> 00:17:25,837
I wasn't going to show it to you
because it's over your budget,

260
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:28,131
but the gentleman here
was being so particular

261
00:17:28,214 --> 00:17:29,883
that I had no other choice.

262
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:32,886
This place faces south,

263
00:17:32,969 --> 00:17:35,555
has great water pressure,
quiet neighbors upstairs,

264
00:17:35,638 --> 00:17:37,891
and security cameras. Everything.

265
00:17:38,516 --> 00:17:40,602
If you can afford it, take it.

266
00:17:40,685 --> 00:17:42,645
We've seen more than enough properties.

267
00:17:42,729 --> 00:17:44,564
Let me check myself.

268
00:17:48,151 --> 00:17:51,446
Your husband is very thorough.

269
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:55,742
But then, if a guy like that
is only generous to you,

270
00:17:55,825 --> 00:17:57,327
it's game over.

271
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:04,375
The water pressure is good.
No noise from upstairs either.

272
00:18:04,459 --> 00:18:06,085
-However…
-What now?

273
00:18:06,169 --> 00:18:07,962
A lot of places put up
dummy cameras these days.

274
00:18:08,046 --> 00:18:09,631
Are these actually working?

275
00:18:09,714 --> 00:18:12,258
I'll go check
with the management office myself.

276
00:18:13,510 --> 00:18:14,886
You two look around.

277
00:18:24,312 --> 00:18:26,314
This place gets
really great natural light.

278
00:18:27,857 --> 00:18:28,775
Yes.

279
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:31,027
This is the best
out of all the properties we viewed today.

280
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:33,154
It's that much more expensive too.

281
00:18:33,238 --> 00:18:36,324
Plus, it's too big for me to live alone.

282
00:18:39,536 --> 00:18:40,370
In that case,

283
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:42,497
how about we live together?

284
00:18:43,164 --> 00:18:44,249
-Sorry?
-It could be here,

285
00:18:44,332 --> 00:18:47,043
or my place is good too.
Living together is an option.

286
00:18:48,503 --> 00:18:49,963
Are you asking me to move in with you?

287
00:18:54,551 --> 00:18:56,678
Right now,
you have a few different options.

288
00:18:56,761 --> 00:18:59,514
You could take out a loan
and move in here,

289
00:18:59,597 --> 00:19:02,392
or look for a cheaper place
that fits your budget,

290
00:19:02,475 --> 00:19:05,019
or even stretch yourself
and look into buying a home.

291
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:08,189
And you could consider

292
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:10,608
marriage as one of the options.

293
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:19,617
Wait, is this a proposal?

294
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:23,746
I'm ready to do that at any time,

295
00:19:24,622 --> 00:19:28,334
but today, I'm presenting it
as one of your housing options.

296
00:19:29,627 --> 00:19:31,504
It never once crossed my mind

297
00:19:33,006 --> 00:19:34,007
that marriage

298
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:37,552
could be one of my housing options.

299
00:19:38,970 --> 00:19:42,682
Well, think it over
while you're staying at my place.

300
00:19:48,021 --> 00:19:49,439
Why? Do I look pretty?

301
00:19:49,522 --> 00:19:50,398
Yeah, you do.

302
00:19:52,025 --> 00:19:53,276
Like I didn't know that.

303
00:19:56,654 --> 00:19:57,822
Hello.

304
00:19:58,489 --> 00:20:00,408
Do you speak French?

305
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:01,701
Yes.

306
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:02,952
Come on, help them.

307
00:20:04,954 --> 00:20:05,788
You should try it.

308
00:20:05,872 --> 00:20:06,956
Huh?

309
00:20:13,046 --> 00:20:14,297
Can I help you?

310
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:15,882
Oh, yes. So…

311
00:20:16,591 --> 00:20:17,592
This place.

312
00:20:17,675 --> 00:20:19,302
How do I get there?

313
00:20:19,969 --> 00:20:21,262
Go straight.

314
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:26,851
At the roundabout. Go 50 meters.

315
00:20:26,935 --> 00:20:29,604
You'll see the sign.

316
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:31,648
I'm sorry, could you repeat that?

317
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,151
Straight.

318
00:20:36,694 --> 00:20:38,279
Roundabout.

319
00:20:38,363 --> 00:20:40,114
See the sign.

320
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,618
Okay, I get it.

321
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:46,537
It was hard
because not many people here speak French.

322
00:20:46,621 --> 00:20:47,664
Thank you so much.

323
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:50,333
-Thank you.
-My pleasure.

324
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:51,584
-Have a nice trip!
-Thank you.

325
00:20:51,668 --> 00:20:52,752
Thank you. Have a nice day.

326
00:20:55,838 --> 00:20:57,382
They actually understood my French!

327
00:20:58,257 --> 00:20:59,425
Great job.

328
00:21:00,009 --> 00:21:02,178
I don't think
they understood at first, though.

329
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:04,013
Your pronunciation was a bit off,

330
00:21:04,097 --> 00:21:05,848
and you paired a masculine noun
with a feminine article.

331
00:21:05,932 --> 00:21:06,808
Did I?

332
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:11,938
French is too difficult
because of the genders.

333
00:21:12,021 --> 00:21:15,149
This won't do.
I'll just have to teach you a lot more.

334
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:16,067
Teach me what?

335
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:18,611
Gender differences.

336
00:21:51,144 --> 00:21:52,186
FRENCH LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY TEST

337
00:21:56,441 --> 00:21:57,817
You're really just studying.

338
00:21:58,401 --> 00:21:59,318
Let me quiz you.

339
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:01,154
Okay.

340
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:09,037
Is "beard" masculine or feminine?

341
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:11,289
Masculine, obviously.

342
00:22:11,372 --> 00:22:13,291
Wrong. It's feminine.

343
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:15,043
Really?

344
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:16,544
Then,

345
00:22:18,171 --> 00:22:19,338
what about hair?

346
00:22:22,425 --> 00:22:23,676
Feminine?

347
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,595
Nope. Masculine.

348
00:22:27,638 --> 00:22:29,891
All these gender rules are so difficult.

349
00:22:29,974 --> 00:22:32,602
That's why you can't use logic with this.

350
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:33,770
You just memorize it.

351
00:22:40,943 --> 00:22:41,903
What about this?

352
00:22:41,986 --> 00:22:43,029
I know this one.

353
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:46,032
La bise. It's feminine.

354
00:22:46,991 --> 00:22:48,534
What about what you and I are doing?

355
00:22:49,911 --> 00:22:51,662
What you and I are doing?

356
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:54,457
Embrasser.

357
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:57,293
It's not a noun. It's a verb.

358
00:23:52,557 --> 00:23:55,810
FRENCH LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY EXAM

359
00:24:05,403 --> 00:24:06,529
Put your clothes in here.

360
00:24:06,612 --> 00:24:09,532
There's a lot of empty space
in your place.

361
00:24:10,116 --> 00:24:11,701
It's a bit big for one person, right?

362
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:14,036
Come out once you're done unpacking.
I'll make tea.

363
00:24:14,662 --> 00:24:15,496
Okay.

364
00:24:31,679 --> 00:24:33,764
I received the strangest proposal.

365
00:24:35,892 --> 00:24:39,604
It was nothing like the one
I had made in the past.

366
00:24:43,399 --> 00:24:46,402
It wasn't emotional or impulsive.

367
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:48,112
It was a rational and calm suggestion.

368
00:24:50,781 --> 00:24:51,657
That's right.

369
00:24:51,741 --> 00:24:53,618
This is how you get married.

370
00:25:14,013 --> 00:25:14,889
But then…

371
00:25:16,390 --> 00:25:17,975
why am I feeling this way?

372
00:25:21,187 --> 00:25:24,857
I love Mr. Kang so much,
and I don't want us to ever break up.

373
00:25:26,234 --> 00:25:27,526
So why?

374
00:25:27,610 --> 00:25:29,195
Why am I hesitating?

375
00:25:40,456 --> 00:25:41,791
Ms. Cha! Congratulations.

376
00:25:41,874 --> 00:25:43,542
Why? What for?

377
00:25:43,626 --> 00:25:44,877
You're getting a promotion.

378
00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:48,130
What do you mean?
It's not even promotion season yet.

379
00:25:48,714 --> 00:25:50,091
It's a special promotion!

380
00:25:52,260 --> 00:25:55,179
Manager Cha Ji-yoon,
how are you going to lead a team

381
00:25:55,263 --> 00:25:57,598
when you're so slow on the uptake?

382
00:25:58,099 --> 00:26:00,184
Mr. Jeon is also
a special promotion candidate.

383
00:26:00,268 --> 00:26:01,227
Really?

384
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:04,939
Gosh, finally!
I'm finally becoming a Sr. Associate!

385
00:26:05,690 --> 00:26:07,483
The President recommended you both,

386
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:10,653
and Mr. Kang even submitted
proof of your contributions to HR.

387
00:26:11,696 --> 00:26:14,615
I'm so jealous.
I should've applied to the task force too.

388
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:18,202
Not everyone who applies gets accepted.

389
00:26:19,704 --> 00:26:22,206
And not everyone who gets accepted
gets a special promotion.

390
00:26:22,290 --> 00:26:25,251
Well, it's your turn soon, Ms. Shin.

391
00:26:25,334 --> 00:26:27,503
You're a great marketer,
so you'll get it after the launch.

392
00:26:28,671 --> 00:26:29,630
Thanks for saying that.

393
00:26:31,173 --> 00:26:34,093
Excuse me, little ones.
Could you keep your attention on me?

394
00:26:34,176 --> 00:26:35,803
It's only a recommendation.

395
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:38,806
Who knows what will happen
when the HR team starts vetting?

396
00:26:38,889 --> 00:26:40,266
Don't get ahead of yourself.

397
00:26:40,349 --> 00:26:41,600
No way.

398
00:26:41,684 --> 00:26:43,769
I already bragged to my wife about it.

399
00:26:43,853 --> 00:26:46,564
Don't jinx it.

400
00:27:38,074 --> 00:27:41,035
Don't get ahead of yourself
until the final results are out.

401
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:43,412
But still, congratulations.

402
00:27:47,541 --> 00:27:48,417
Hang on.

403
00:27:49,543 --> 00:27:50,711
If I want to keep climbing the ladder,

404
00:27:51,629 --> 00:27:53,798
wouldn't it be better not to get married?

405
00:27:56,967 --> 00:27:58,594
-Ms. Cha.
-Yeah?

406
00:27:58,677 --> 00:28:00,137
Mr. Jeon says it's time to leave.

407
00:28:01,138 --> 00:28:01,972
I'll be right there.

408
00:28:11,816 --> 00:28:14,276
President Han is married too, right?

409
00:28:21,909 --> 00:28:23,202
Home-AI Zone…

410
00:28:24,203 --> 00:28:25,037
It's not feasible.

411
00:28:25,121 --> 00:28:26,580
-Sorry?
-Pardon?

412
00:28:26,664 --> 00:28:29,500
It wouldn't be fair
to our other partner companies.

413
00:28:31,085 --> 00:28:32,294
My apologies.

414
00:28:32,378 --> 00:28:34,547
Well, could you think it over

415
00:28:35,464 --> 00:28:37,049
again, perhaps?

416
00:28:38,092 --> 00:28:39,051
We understand.

417
00:28:39,385 --> 00:28:42,304
We'll come back
with a convincing proposal.

418
00:28:42,388 --> 00:28:43,347
Well, okay.

419
00:28:49,687 --> 00:28:50,646
Nothing comes easy.

420
00:28:51,063 --> 00:28:53,190
If they accepted our offer,

421
00:28:53,691 --> 00:28:56,277
our competitors
would obviously throw a fit.

422
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:57,445
But honey,

423
00:28:57,528 --> 00:29:00,489
buying high-end appliances from the start
saves us money in the long run.

424
00:29:00,573 --> 00:29:03,534
Let's just buy them later,
when we move to a larger place.

425
00:29:03,617 --> 00:29:04,827
And when would that be?

426
00:29:04,910 --> 00:29:06,328
Forget it, I'm not marrying you.

427
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:07,955
That again?

428
00:29:08,456 --> 00:29:09,623
When are you going to marry me?

429
00:29:11,667 --> 00:29:13,919
-Don't go. We're here, so let's decide.
-Classic.

430
00:29:14,003 --> 00:29:16,130
Every marriage starts with a good fight.

431
00:29:18,174 --> 00:29:19,425
Do you really fight that much?

432
00:29:23,929 --> 00:29:26,599
We fought over what to watch on TV,

433
00:29:27,516 --> 00:29:29,643
over going out to eat
versus eating at home,

434
00:29:30,436 --> 00:29:32,021
over how we treat my parents versus hers.

435
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:34,231
Man, we fought so much
when we were newlyweds.

436
00:29:34,315 --> 00:29:36,442
Then how do you make it work?

437
00:29:37,735 --> 00:29:39,195
It's like riding an invisible seesaw.

438
00:29:39,820 --> 00:29:42,281
I take this, so I'll let go of that.

439
00:29:42,364 --> 00:29:45,326
You let it slide last time,
so I look the other way this time.

440
00:29:45,409 --> 00:29:47,912
You find balance
while rocking back and forth like that.

441
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:50,748
Sounds exhausting just hearing about it.

442
00:29:50,831 --> 00:29:51,832
Well,

443
00:29:52,666 --> 00:29:54,043
you get the hang of it after a while.

444
00:29:55,002 --> 00:29:56,795
When it feels tense,
quickly run and do some chores.

445
00:29:56,879 --> 00:29:58,506
But what if the seesaw tips too far?

446
00:29:58,589 --> 00:29:59,757
Then it explodes.

447
00:30:00,424 --> 00:30:02,885
Married couples fight. It's inevitable.

448
00:30:02,968 --> 00:30:05,221
What matters is how you make up afterward.

449
00:30:05,304 --> 00:30:06,764
And how do you two make up?

450
00:30:06,847 --> 00:30:09,600
We made a rule to keep our mouths shut

451
00:30:09,683 --> 00:30:11,393
but stay within each other's eyeshot.

452
00:30:12,269 --> 00:30:14,021
Neither of us is allowed to storm out.

453
00:30:16,065 --> 00:30:17,483
That's not easy at all.

454
00:30:17,983 --> 00:30:19,735
Why? Did Mr. Kang ask you to marry him?

455
00:30:23,030 --> 00:30:24,907
Oh, my stomach.
I have to run to the restroom.

456
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:25,991
I'll be right back.

457
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,370
What did you just say?

458
00:30:29,954 --> 00:30:31,205
I'm going to the restroom.

459
00:30:31,705 --> 00:30:32,831
Hey, Jeon Kee-tae.

460
00:30:32,915 --> 00:30:33,916
Stop right there!

461
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:35,376
Hey!

462
00:30:44,218 --> 00:30:45,344
I must've been careless.

463
00:30:46,011 --> 00:30:48,472
Kee-tae knows all about us.

464
00:30:48,556 --> 00:30:49,932
And rumors haven't spread yet?

465
00:30:50,683 --> 00:30:52,768
Thankfully, he said he hasn't told a soul

466
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:53,978
and he never will.

467
00:30:55,479 --> 00:30:57,314
Looks like Mr. Jeon is quite loyal.

468
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:04,655
Why do you keep your tea so far away?

469
00:31:04,738 --> 00:31:06,407
If you leave it out here,

470
00:31:06,490 --> 00:31:08,284
it'd be easier to find and drink it.

471
00:31:09,618 --> 00:31:11,328
I don't like having stuff lying around.

472
00:31:13,289 --> 00:31:14,832
I need these to be
in my view to take them.

473
00:31:14,915 --> 00:31:16,208
I'll just put these back.

474
00:31:16,292 --> 00:31:17,167
No,

475
00:31:17,918 --> 00:31:20,045
leave them here. Whatever works for you.

476
00:31:30,806 --> 00:31:33,183
I guess you sleep well
only when it's completely dark.

477
00:31:33,267 --> 00:31:35,561
Yes. Is that not the case for you?

478
00:31:35,644 --> 00:31:39,064
To be honest,
I can't sleep well if it's too dark.

479
00:31:39,481 --> 00:31:40,316
Oh.

480
00:31:41,191 --> 00:31:42,401
You should've told me sooner.

481
00:31:50,034 --> 00:31:51,035
Mr. Kang.

482
00:31:51,660 --> 00:31:53,579
Are you always going to
change your ways for me?

483
00:31:54,413 --> 00:31:55,247
Of course, I am.

484
00:31:55,331 --> 00:31:56,498
But for how long?

485
00:31:57,958 --> 00:32:00,419
It's fine for now,
but you can't do that forever.

486
00:32:02,296 --> 00:32:03,589
Would that be too hard?

487
00:32:03,672 --> 00:32:06,550
Someone told me that marriage
is like riding a seesaw.

488
00:32:07,801 --> 00:32:09,553
One person gives in this time,

489
00:32:09,637 --> 00:32:11,764
and the other gives in the next time.

490
00:32:11,847 --> 00:32:13,766
If only one side keeps giving in,

491
00:32:13,849 --> 00:32:15,809
the seesaw won't move anymore.

492
00:32:18,854 --> 00:32:21,357
Let's figure out our own way of things.

493
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:28,656
Would I be able to set aside

494
00:32:29,281 --> 00:32:32,201
my way of doing things
just for Mr. Kang too?

495
00:32:34,745 --> 00:32:40,751
6:00 A.M.
WAKE UP

496
00:35:01,809 --> 00:35:03,602
These moments feel like a gift,

497
00:35:03,685 --> 00:35:06,063
and I would've never known
if we didn't stay together.

498
00:35:07,189 --> 00:35:08,023
Good morning.

499
00:35:09,942 --> 00:35:10,984
You should've woken me up.

500
00:35:11,068 --> 00:35:12,986
I could've heard
more of your singing then.

501
00:35:15,697 --> 00:35:17,533
You'll hear a lot of it in the future.

502
00:35:22,204 --> 00:35:23,497
I'm all ready.

503
00:35:23,580 --> 00:35:24,498
Let's go, Mr. Kang.

504
00:35:28,585 --> 00:35:30,295
You look beautiful the way you are, but…

505
00:35:42,099 --> 00:35:47,437
SI-WOO'S, JI-YOON'S

506
00:35:48,021 --> 00:35:51,650
It's ridiculous that Ms. Cha
will hold the same title as us.

507
00:35:52,276 --> 00:35:55,779
We should stop this,
even if it means taking collective action.

508
00:35:55,863 --> 00:35:57,239
We can't just sit back and watch.

509
00:35:57,823 --> 00:36:01,118
Exactly. If she stayed under me,
I would've given her the worst review.

510
00:36:02,578 --> 00:36:05,080
Did you all see
the Global Talent Development Program?

511
00:36:09,626 --> 00:36:10,502
GLOBAL TALENT DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM

512
00:36:12,838 --> 00:36:14,298
What's the point?

513
00:36:14,673 --> 00:36:16,383
Married guys like me can't go anywhere.

514
00:36:16,967 --> 00:36:19,177
I want to run away right now
because of our boss,

515
00:36:19,261 --> 00:36:21,179
but I don't meet the requirements.

516
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:27,394
ASSIGNMENT COUNTRIES:
RUSSIA, DUBAI, SENEGAL, VIETNAM

517
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,649
They pay for living expenses
on top of your salary?

518
00:36:32,733 --> 00:36:33,984
Wow, what a steal.

519
00:36:35,903 --> 00:36:36,737
Haha.

520
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:39,907
You need at least three years' experience
with good performance reviews,

521
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:41,074
Mr. First-year.

522
00:36:41,575 --> 00:36:43,827
GLOBAL TALENT DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM
REGIONAL SPECIALIST RECRUITMENT

523
00:36:44,703 --> 00:36:46,371
Regional specialist, huh?

524
00:36:49,082 --> 00:36:50,125
Okay, got it.

525
00:36:53,170 --> 00:36:55,130
Hey, shouldn't you all be
at the design meeting?

526
00:36:56,256 --> 00:36:58,383
But the meeting is next week.

527
00:36:58,467 --> 00:37:01,094
The Design Team
is at an exhibition until today.

528
00:37:01,178 --> 00:37:04,306
How many times do I have to tell you
to report things like that right away?!

529
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:06,183
But I did tell you.

530
00:37:06,266 --> 00:37:07,851
Ugh, seriously…

531
00:37:10,854 --> 00:37:12,648
Geez. Ugh!

532
00:37:13,815 --> 00:37:14,816
Ugh!

533
00:37:26,828 --> 00:37:29,081
How much longer
do I have to endure Mr. Ko?

534
00:37:29,164 --> 00:37:30,958
Just wait a little bit.

535
00:37:31,041 --> 00:37:32,626
You delivered results,

536
00:37:32,709 --> 00:37:34,878
so you should be able to move
to a team you want.

537
00:37:37,214 --> 00:37:39,716
Ms. Cha, have you ever been to Senegal?

538
00:37:40,676 --> 00:37:43,887
Are you talking about
the Global Talent Development Program?

539
00:37:44,721 --> 00:37:45,847
Yes.

540
00:37:45,931 --> 00:37:49,726
Ever since I saw Senegal on that list,
it won't leave my mind.

541
00:37:49,810 --> 00:37:51,228
It'd be amazing if you went.

542
00:37:51,311 --> 00:37:56,233
Most people are scared to take the leap,
but you'll definitely level up if you go.

543
00:37:56,316 --> 00:37:57,901
They could assign you
as an expat later too.

544
00:37:59,069 --> 00:38:01,780
I'm scared, though.
It's not like all applicants get accepted.

545
00:38:03,615 --> 00:38:05,075
Have you never thought about it?

546
00:38:06,493 --> 00:38:09,955
I would have thought about it
if I were still under Mr. Ko,

547
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:11,581
but I can't go now.

548
00:38:11,665 --> 00:38:13,166
Because of Mr. Kang?

549
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:16,586
Yeah, I don't want to leave him alone.

550
00:38:18,088 --> 00:38:18,922
Gosh.

551
00:38:20,173 --> 00:38:22,676
At this rate, you'll say you'll marry him.

552
00:38:24,094 --> 00:38:25,053
I used to think

553
00:38:26,013 --> 00:38:28,515
that marriage
was the natural ending to dating,

554
00:38:29,808 --> 00:38:32,894
and that as long as
you loved each other, that was enough.

555
00:38:33,979 --> 00:38:36,356
But not anymore.
There's so much to think about.

556
00:38:37,024 --> 00:38:38,191
Like what?

557
00:38:38,275 --> 00:38:41,653
Whether getting married
will get in the way of my career,

558
00:38:41,737 --> 00:38:44,406
whether I can genuinely live well
with this person,

559
00:38:45,073 --> 00:38:46,450
and most of all,

560
00:38:46,533 --> 00:38:50,037
whether I am absolutely certain
that we'll never break up.

561
00:38:51,204 --> 00:38:52,414
Why are you so intense?

562
00:38:52,497 --> 00:38:54,583
Plenty of people get married
and get a divorce.

563
00:38:57,252 --> 00:38:58,420
I can't be one of them.

564
00:39:00,130 --> 00:39:01,173
I just can't

565
00:39:02,007 --> 00:39:05,010
let him experience failure twice.

566
00:39:09,056 --> 00:39:09,931
You're living together?

567
00:39:10,015 --> 00:39:12,309
I clearly said, "for the time being."

568
00:39:12,392 --> 00:39:14,061
Technicality's not what matters here.

569
00:39:14,686 --> 00:39:18,065
Have you ever lived
with another person in the last ten years?

570
00:39:18,148 --> 00:39:19,274
No.

571
00:39:19,357 --> 00:39:21,693
So are you okay?
You're notoriously particular.

572
00:39:21,777 --> 00:39:24,112
Of course, I was also worried at first

573
00:39:24,196 --> 00:39:26,239
about whether I could live
with another person.

574
00:39:27,074 --> 00:39:29,534
But actually,
it's not as bad as I thought.

575
00:39:29,618 --> 00:39:31,453
Actually, it's great. Really great.

576
00:39:31,536 --> 00:39:32,621
Wow.

577
00:39:33,205 --> 00:39:37,084
Love really is the only thing
that can change a person.

578
00:39:44,299 --> 00:39:47,219
Even so, how could you propose by saying

579
00:39:47,302 --> 00:39:49,638
getting married is
one of her housing options?

580
00:39:49,721 --> 00:39:52,474
You should do it properly
with a ring and flowers.

581
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:55,102
Then it'd become too difficult
for her to say no.

582
00:39:55,185 --> 00:39:57,270
I didn't want to make her feel pressured.

583
00:39:57,854 --> 00:40:00,857
But don't you think Ms. Ji-yoon
felt a bit disappointed?

584
00:40:02,567 --> 00:40:05,070
She might be wondering
if you were being serious at all.

585
00:40:33,223 --> 00:40:34,516
Why do you keep following me?

586
00:40:35,267 --> 00:40:36,143
Because you're beautiful.

587
00:40:37,394 --> 00:40:39,688
If you're just doing this
because of my looks,

588
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:40,772
I'll pass.

589
00:40:40,856 --> 00:40:43,900
I need a man
who appreciates my inner beauty.

590
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:46,153
You should just give up now.

591
00:40:46,945 --> 00:40:48,071
You've got me all wrong.

592
00:40:48,155 --> 00:40:49,948
I'm only looking at your inner beauty.

593
00:40:53,577 --> 00:40:54,995
Another wrong answer today?

594
00:40:55,078 --> 00:40:56,163
Yes.

595
00:40:56,246 --> 00:40:58,456
You really need to change your approach.

596
00:41:12,762 --> 00:41:14,139
Then how about this?

597
00:41:15,724 --> 00:41:17,267
What is this thing?

598
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:20,645
It's my feelings for you.
Not too heavy, but definitely not shallow.

599
00:41:23,648 --> 00:41:25,859
It means you don't have to feel bad
about saying no,

600
00:41:25,942 --> 00:41:30,155
and you should think it through seriously,
for your own sake.

601
00:41:32,407 --> 00:41:33,825
I guess I like rings.

602
00:41:34,701 --> 00:41:37,329
I almost forgot
that I was even contemplating.

603
00:41:38,997 --> 00:41:41,374
Then keep contemplating,
until you finish eating that.

604
00:41:41,791 --> 00:41:43,126
I'm going to really savor it.

605
00:41:47,964 --> 00:41:49,466
This thing is huge, isn't it?

606
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:01,019
Mr. Noh,

607
00:42:01,102 --> 00:42:02,687
would you be up for a bite together?

608
00:42:02,771 --> 00:42:05,523
Please give me one more chance.
I'll make sure to deliver this time.

609
00:42:07,067 --> 00:42:08,068
Mr. Noh!

610
00:42:08,151 --> 00:42:10,654
I just discovered some shocking news.

611
00:42:11,905 --> 00:42:14,366
MANAGING DIRECTOR NOH

612
00:42:27,337 --> 00:42:29,506
You love taking credit
for other people's work,

613
00:42:29,589 --> 00:42:31,299
and now you give all of that to Ms. Cha?

614
00:42:31,383 --> 00:42:33,426
Why? To screw me over?

615
00:42:34,594 --> 00:42:37,180
Are you that terrified
I'll make Managing Director before you?

616
00:42:37,264 --> 00:42:39,641
I'm not intimidated by incompetent people.

617
00:42:39,724 --> 00:42:41,184
Especially those who play dirty.

618
00:42:43,436 --> 00:42:46,815
-You haven't learned your lesson, huh?
-It looks like you're the one who hasn't.

619
00:42:47,941 --> 00:42:50,026
Are you sure the lifeline
you're holding onto

620
00:42:50,110 --> 00:42:51,444
is actually reliable?

621
00:42:52,737 --> 00:42:54,781
At this rate,
you might end up working under Ms. Cha.

622
00:42:54,864 --> 00:42:56,700
Why, you little…

623
00:42:57,617 --> 00:42:59,828
I may not be able
to lift you up the ladder,

624
00:42:59,911 --> 00:43:01,871
but I can drag you straight to the bottom!

625
00:43:12,799 --> 00:43:13,717
Be my guest.

626
00:43:24,978 --> 00:43:26,521
That little…

627
00:43:28,064 --> 00:43:29,316
Good luck with wedding planning.

628
00:43:29,399 --> 00:43:30,233
Thanks.

629
00:43:31,026 --> 00:43:32,319
I'll head out now.

630
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:34,738
She's getting married next month,

631
00:43:34,821 --> 00:43:36,364
and she's already moving teams?

632
00:43:36,448 --> 00:43:37,574
See you.

633
00:43:37,657 --> 00:43:39,242
-Stay in touch.
-Of course.

634
00:43:39,326 --> 00:43:40,410
-I totally forgot.
-Bye.

635
00:43:40,493 --> 00:43:41,661
Get home safe.

636
00:43:41,745 --> 00:43:42,662
Forgot what?

637
00:43:42,746 --> 00:43:46,207
That office couples aren't allowed
to work on the same team.

638
00:43:46,291 --> 00:43:48,752
It's not that they can't,
they choose not to.

639
00:43:48,835 --> 00:43:50,378
It'd be awkward to work together.

640
00:43:50,962 --> 00:43:51,796
Is that right?

641
00:43:55,008 --> 00:43:58,720
But it means one person might be forced
to give up the work they want to do.

642
00:43:58,803 --> 00:44:00,096
Right.

643
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:01,306
And let's be real,

644
00:44:02,349 --> 00:44:03,975
it's usually the one who's more junior.

645
00:44:05,894 --> 00:44:07,437
Marrying a colleague is a bad idea.

646
00:44:12,692 --> 00:44:14,861
Double-check that and show me, okay?

647
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:16,613
Great work.

648
00:44:34,381 --> 00:44:36,299
-Ms. Choi?
-Yes?

649
00:44:47,310 --> 00:44:50,397
-Ms. Choi, we'll get the proposal copied.
-That was enough.

650
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:52,107
Thank you.

651
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:53,566
Ji-yoon.

652
00:44:54,484 --> 00:44:55,402
Ms. Choi.

653
00:44:58,947 --> 00:45:00,240
I heard.

654
00:45:03,910 --> 00:45:04,744
Thank you.

655
00:45:08,248 --> 00:45:09,207
See you.

656
00:45:21,010 --> 00:45:22,929
-A themed zone?
-Yes.

657
00:45:23,012 --> 00:45:25,598
In exchange for us
creating our Home-AI Zone,

658
00:45:25,682 --> 00:45:28,726
we propose letting our competitors
set up their own themed zones too.

659
00:45:28,810 --> 00:45:30,687
Is it necessary to go to such lengths?

660
00:45:30,770 --> 00:45:33,398
If it means we can set up
our Home-AI Zone,

661
00:45:33,481 --> 00:45:34,732
then why not?

662
00:45:34,816 --> 00:45:35,900
It'd be to our benefit.

663
00:45:36,401 --> 00:45:38,069
And what's your reasoning behind that?

664
00:45:38,153 --> 00:45:39,571
Given the current market structure,

665
00:45:39,654 --> 00:45:42,574
running ahead on our own
won't win us any applause.

666
00:45:42,657 --> 00:45:45,994
We need to make sure our partners
and competitors grow with us.

667
00:45:46,077 --> 00:45:49,205
The trick is
to stay exactly half a step ahead.

668
00:45:49,289 --> 00:45:52,667
Frankly, I'm sure we'll win regardless
of what themed zone they bring in.

669
00:45:54,252 --> 00:45:55,170
I knew it.

670
00:45:56,296 --> 00:45:58,673
-I wasn't wrong about you.
-Sorry?

671
00:45:58,756 --> 00:46:01,843
Following you around to get you
on the task force was worth it.

672
00:46:05,346 --> 00:46:06,347
But then,

673
00:46:07,265 --> 00:46:10,018
I'll have to move
to another team if we get married.

674
00:46:11,019 --> 00:46:11,853
Says who?

675
00:46:11,936 --> 00:46:13,188
Company policy.

676
00:46:13,646 --> 00:46:15,565
Married couples can't work
on the same team.

677
00:46:15,648 --> 00:46:18,526
Right, but why would you
be the one to move?

678
00:46:19,194 --> 00:46:20,320
I'll be the one to move.

679
00:46:25,241 --> 00:46:26,159
Mr. Kang.

680
00:46:27,118 --> 00:46:28,578
I'm going back to my place today.

681
00:46:30,914 --> 00:46:33,791
-Why?
-The police called this afternoon.

682
00:46:34,292 --> 00:46:35,335
They caught the burglar.

683
00:46:38,338 --> 00:46:39,172
That's a relief.

684
00:46:40,882 --> 00:46:43,092
I'm still a bit scared, though.

685
00:46:43,176 --> 00:46:45,011
So could you stay with me tonight?

686
00:46:46,930 --> 00:46:47,847
Sure.

687
00:46:51,142 --> 00:46:53,102
Is your contemplation finally over?

688
00:46:54,562 --> 00:46:55,396
Yes.

689
00:46:57,232 --> 00:46:58,525
And did you find the answer?

690
00:46:59,567 --> 00:47:00,401
Yes.

691
00:47:01,611 --> 00:47:04,405
Regarding the housing option you proposed…

692
00:47:12,664 --> 00:47:13,623
A burglar?

693
00:47:21,548 --> 00:47:22,674
Stay here.

694
00:47:34,727 --> 00:47:35,687
Holy crap.

695
00:47:36,271 --> 00:47:37,480
Why are you standing there?

696
00:47:48,992 --> 00:47:49,909
Dad.

697
00:47:53,079 --> 00:47:55,582
Dad, just take a seat. Sit down and--

698
00:47:55,665 --> 00:47:57,166
Ms. Ji-yoon and I are dating.

699
00:47:59,210 --> 00:48:00,044
You…

700
00:48:00,670 --> 00:48:01,879
I'm sorry, Dad.

701
00:48:01,963 --> 00:48:03,423
I should've told you sooner.

702
00:48:06,676 --> 00:48:07,510
Outside.

703
00:48:15,810 --> 00:48:16,686
Dad.

704
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:19,772
Stay here. I'll go talk to him.

705
00:48:27,780 --> 00:48:29,532
You should've called me before coming!

706
00:48:29,616 --> 00:48:31,034
I did,

707
00:48:31,117 --> 00:48:33,119
but you didn't pick up.

708
00:48:36,664 --> 00:48:39,375
We thought you were out,
so we just came to drop off the kimchi.

709
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:43,880
That guy.
He's the one from the kiss cam, right?

710
00:48:45,673 --> 00:48:46,799
But how does Dad know him?

711
00:48:46,883 --> 00:48:48,718
Don't say anything to Mom, okay?

712
00:48:58,978 --> 00:49:00,104
You should pace yourself.

713
00:49:01,356 --> 00:49:02,398
When did it start?

714
00:49:03,024 --> 00:49:06,319
We first met in the summer
and started dating in the fall.

715
00:49:07,028 --> 00:49:08,655
And now it's snowy winter.

716
00:49:10,740 --> 00:49:12,408
I've been in the dark for that long, huh?

717
00:49:13,117 --> 00:49:14,202
I'm sorry, sir.

718
00:49:16,454 --> 00:49:17,372
Come to think of it,

719
00:49:18,873 --> 00:49:21,292
I never even asked
what company you work at.

720
00:49:22,168 --> 00:49:23,795
That's why I like you so much.

721
00:49:24,837 --> 00:49:27,632
You never asked what I do for a living,
what school I went to,

722
00:49:27,715 --> 00:49:29,008
or how much money I make.

723
00:49:29,717 --> 00:49:31,511
You didn't ask any of that.

724
00:49:32,470 --> 00:49:33,471
You just

725
00:49:35,056 --> 00:49:36,432
saw me for who I am.

726
00:49:38,851 --> 00:49:40,353
Well, I'm regretting it now.

727
00:49:43,439 --> 00:49:45,108
Then let me ask you this straight up.

728
00:49:47,944 --> 00:49:49,112
Are you seeing my daughter

729
00:49:50,655 --> 00:49:52,240
with marriage in mind?

730
00:49:53,408 --> 00:49:55,952
You're going to be upset
no matter how I answer that question.

731
00:49:56,035 --> 00:49:57,036
You're damn right.

732
00:49:57,995 --> 00:49:59,038
Yeah, I'm upset.

733
00:50:01,791 --> 00:50:02,834
You're laughing? You punk.

734
00:50:08,923 --> 00:50:10,758
I know what you're worried about

735
00:50:11,467 --> 00:50:12,677
better than anyone else.

736
00:50:14,303 --> 00:50:16,013
But I can tell you this with certainty.

737
00:50:18,224 --> 00:50:21,644
I deeply care for Ms. Ji-yoon.

738
00:50:33,698 --> 00:50:34,532
Fine.

739
00:50:36,534 --> 00:50:38,161
It's not like you're children.

740
00:50:39,245 --> 00:50:41,748
You're smart grown-ups,
so you must know what you're doing.

741
00:50:42,665 --> 00:50:43,750
But still,

742
00:50:45,293 --> 00:50:46,794
I'm against this for now.

743
00:50:48,588 --> 00:50:50,173
I don't care if you're upset.

744
00:50:57,555 --> 00:50:58,473
Okay.

745
00:51:10,359 --> 00:51:11,319
You punk.

746
00:51:12,779 --> 00:51:14,322
Why did it have to be my Ji-yoon?

747
00:51:20,411 --> 00:51:21,370
Geez.

748
00:51:29,003 --> 00:51:30,838
I'm home.

749
00:51:30,922 --> 00:51:32,548
Goodness, what on earth is going on?

750
00:51:32,632 --> 00:51:34,717
Listen, I'm 100% on my wife's side.

751
00:51:35,551 --> 00:51:38,095
If she says yes, it's a yes.

752
00:51:38,179 --> 00:51:40,014
If she says no, it's a no.

753
00:51:40,890 --> 00:51:41,766
You got that?!

754
00:51:41,849 --> 00:51:44,310
Why are you acting so out of character?

755
00:51:44,393 --> 00:51:46,312
-Where should I set him down?
-Right here.

756
00:51:46,395 --> 00:51:48,272
All right, just lie down for now.

757
00:51:50,274 --> 00:51:51,192
Unbelievable.

758
00:51:53,194 --> 00:51:54,237
Thank you.

759
00:51:54,821 --> 00:51:57,406
He barely touches alcohol.
Why did he drink so much?

760
00:51:59,408 --> 00:52:00,660
Who are you, by the way?

761
00:52:01,494 --> 00:52:03,079
My name is Kang Si-woo.

762
00:52:03,162 --> 00:52:05,206
Well, you're

763
00:52:06,332 --> 00:52:07,458
very good-looking.

764
00:52:09,919 --> 00:52:12,088
How do you know my husband, though?

765
00:52:13,089 --> 00:52:14,340
I'm a regular at his store.

766
00:52:15,883 --> 00:52:18,135
And what line of work
are you in, Mr. Regular?

767
00:52:19,095 --> 00:52:20,596
I work at SAEUM.

768
00:52:20,680 --> 00:52:21,514
Oh my!

769
00:52:21,806 --> 00:52:22,640
Oh my!

770
00:52:24,100 --> 00:52:26,102
Our daughter works there too.

771
00:52:26,185 --> 00:52:28,646
-Her name is Cha Ji-yoon.
-I'm home.

772
00:52:30,648 --> 00:52:31,524
Huh?

773
00:52:32,859 --> 00:52:36,070
Oh, a total stranger.
He scared me a little.

774
00:52:39,365 --> 00:52:40,908
Let me get going.

775
00:52:41,826 --> 00:52:44,161
Please stay for a cup of tea at least.

776
00:52:49,041 --> 00:52:50,293
That's all right.

777
00:52:50,376 --> 00:52:52,587
I'll introduce myself properly next time,

778
00:52:52,670 --> 00:52:53,838
Mother.

779
00:52:56,757 --> 00:52:57,758
Okay, then.

780
00:52:57,842 --> 00:53:00,803
Then let's definitely
meet again next time.

781
00:53:18,237 --> 00:53:20,823
Oh my word. He called me "Mother."

782
00:53:20,907 --> 00:53:21,866
You heard that, right?

783
00:53:22,617 --> 00:53:25,536
Yeah, but I call
older ladies at restaurants that too.

784
00:53:25,620 --> 00:53:26,996
My goodness.

785
00:53:27,496 --> 00:53:29,999
He's so polite
and treats elders so well too.

786
00:53:31,626 --> 00:53:32,960
I wonder if he's married.

787
00:53:49,018 --> 00:53:50,519
My dad gave you an earful, didn't he?

788
00:53:50,603 --> 00:53:54,357
He bought me drinks, gave me advice,
and even put his arm around my shoulder.

789
00:53:54,440 --> 00:53:55,566
Yeah, right.

790
00:53:56,400 --> 00:53:59,111
Come on, spill. What did he actually say?

791
00:53:59,195 --> 00:54:01,280
That's a secret
between your father and me.

792
00:54:03,824 --> 00:54:06,285
I should've told him sooner like you said.

793
00:54:06,369 --> 00:54:08,120
Things would've gone better then, right?

794
00:54:08,204 --> 00:54:10,998
No, it just means
today was the right time to do it.

795
00:54:11,666 --> 00:54:14,251
A day to get caught
without time to prepare or get nervous.

796
00:54:19,632 --> 00:54:20,758
Shall we walk for a bit?

797
00:54:33,938 --> 00:54:36,983
We met in the summer,
and it's already winter now.

798
00:54:38,317 --> 00:54:40,403
Now we just need to spend spring together,

799
00:54:40,486 --> 00:54:41,487
right?

800
00:54:41,570 --> 00:54:43,322
The first spring
we welcome together, right?

801
00:54:43,906 --> 00:54:45,533
How many springs will there be?

802
00:54:45,616 --> 00:54:48,327
Assuming an average life expectancy of 80,

803
00:54:48,411 --> 00:54:49,578
about 40 springs?

804
00:54:52,498 --> 00:54:55,751
Hearing that I'll be welcoming
40 springs with 1 person

805
00:54:55,835 --> 00:54:57,253
is giving me…

806
00:54:57,336 --> 00:54:58,170
Cold feet?

807
00:54:59,338 --> 00:55:01,257
-A tiny bit.
-I knew it.

808
00:55:02,049 --> 00:55:03,884
I laid out the marriage card too early.

809
00:55:07,096 --> 00:55:10,516
Mr. Kang, are you not afraid of marriage?

810
00:55:11,017 --> 00:55:12,059
Of course, I'm afraid.

811
00:55:12,852 --> 00:55:15,646
I've failed at it once.
So how could I not be?

812
00:55:16,689 --> 00:55:17,732
But?

813
00:55:18,858 --> 00:55:19,900
But it's with you.

814
00:55:23,821 --> 00:55:26,907
I want to see 40 seasons
of cherry blossoms,

815
00:55:26,991 --> 00:55:28,451
40 seasons of fireworks,

816
00:55:28,534 --> 00:55:30,578
autumn leaves, and snow with you.

817
00:55:31,537 --> 00:55:34,707
Sure, marriage can cause pain,
but it has institutional advantages too.

818
00:55:35,332 --> 00:55:38,002
If you ever get sick
or need legal protection,

819
00:55:38,085 --> 00:55:39,920
I can step in as your guardian.

820
00:55:40,004 --> 00:55:42,757
I can give you everything I own as well.

821
00:55:43,841 --> 00:55:44,842
I didn't realize it,

822
00:55:45,843 --> 00:55:47,553
but it really is a tempting suggestion.

823
00:55:48,220 --> 00:55:51,265
The cherry on top is
that I'm older than you.

824
00:55:55,186 --> 00:55:56,020
Mr. Kang.

825
00:55:59,565 --> 00:56:00,733
I don't think

826
00:56:02,026 --> 00:56:03,069
I can choose

827
00:56:03,736 --> 00:56:05,112
the housing option you offered.

828
00:56:07,364 --> 00:56:10,451
I'll look for a place
that's within my budget.

829
00:56:12,328 --> 00:56:13,287
But…

830
00:56:14,330 --> 00:56:15,956
I promise I'll keep

831
00:56:16,832 --> 00:56:18,459
thinking about our marriage.

832
00:56:20,628 --> 00:56:23,756
Then my proposal is on hold, not rejected.

833
00:56:24,673 --> 00:56:27,968
It's a 40-year, long-term project,
so take your time to review it.

834
00:56:28,552 --> 00:56:29,428
Okay.

835
00:56:31,222 --> 00:56:33,140
One day, when my heart's about to burst,

836
00:56:33,224 --> 00:56:36,811
I might answer before you have time
to prepare or get nervous.

837
00:56:38,687 --> 00:56:40,189
I'll be waiting for it.

838
00:57:05,464 --> 00:57:07,925
HOTEL MARINE TERRACE BUSAN
RECEIPT

839
00:57:09,635 --> 00:57:11,178
HOTEL MARINE TERRACE BUSAN
RECEIPT

840
00:57:11,846 --> 00:57:12,763
Finally!

841
00:57:23,899 --> 00:57:24,900
Did you see this?

842
00:57:47,173 --> 00:57:48,382
BLAH BLAH - ANONYMOUS ONLINE COMMUNITY
FOR PROFESSIONALS

843
00:57:48,465 --> 00:57:50,259
OFFICE AFFAIR

844
00:57:51,177 --> 00:57:53,637
I have dirt on a shocking affair
going on at SAEUM.

845
00:57:53,721 --> 00:57:54,972
Anyone curious?

846
00:57:55,055 --> 00:57:57,474
